<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-01T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-01T08:00:00-05:00" n="404" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/192:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece (<persName type="from">MacVeagh</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-01T15:00:00+02:00">November 1, 1933—3 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received November 1—11:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>108. Grounds of refusal cannot be definitely stated till we have had
                                a chance to study documents. Decision apparently admits acts
                                committed were violations of the law in both countries but contends
                                that the proof of criminal intent so far submitted is insufficient.
                                The prosecutor told Harness this morning that he believes the way is
                                thus left open for introduction of new evidence and reopening the
                                case and he is now preparing memorandum on this subject after
                                conference with Solicitor General. Will advise further very shortly.
                                I am seeing Foreign Minister this afternoon.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>